---
description: Ensure frontend user-facing text is Norwegian
globs: app/frontend/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Frontend Language Policy

- All user-facing UI text must be Norwegian (`nb-NO`) in this project.
- Treat English UI copy as development placeholder text that must be replaced before completion.
- This includes:
  - headings, labels, buttons, table headers, empty states, helper text, errors, and notices
  - user-facing strings rendered from React components in `app/frontend`
- Keep internal identifiers in English (variable names, types, function names) unless there is a strong reason not to.

# Quick Checks Before Finishing

- Verify newly added/updated UI strings are Norwegian.
- Remove temporary English placeholders like "Coming soon", "Unknown", "Loading", and similar.
- If a string is intentionally untranslated, add a short comment explaining why.

# Examples

```tsx
// Avoid
<button>Add user</button>

// Prefer
<button>Legg til bruker</button>
```
